HEADWORD: Rudolphine
<hw>Ru*dolph"ine</hw> <pr>(r⟦usdot⟧*d⟦ocr⟧lf"⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a set of astronomical tables
computed by <persfn>Kepler</persfn>, and founded on the observations of
<person>Tycho Brahe</person>; -- so named from
<person><etsep>Rudolph</etsep> II.</person>, emperor of
Germany.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

